<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f9908908312802>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Hand 2 Hand</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sat, May 26th 11:27 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=52719><span id= >Shakaama</span></a><br><span id=notbold>109 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.83]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>level&nbsp;&nbsp;        dmg/dly<br>1              4/36<br>5              5/36<br>10             6/36<br>15             7/36<br>20             8/36<br>25             9/35<br>30             10/34<br>35             11/33<br>40             12/32<br>45             13/31<br>50             14/30<br>60             14/26<br><br>Ok, now FB is 8/20 so you can see that this is good until you hit the 20th - 30th lvls.  Let's assume for a second that you had access to nothing else than a lame fighting baton, and only one.  Now you would equip it in your secondary until lvl 25, then switch it to your primary from then on.  Why? Because the dual wield needs a better dmg/dly ratio in the secondary.  After 30th lvl or so your second hand starts to get a better ratio than the baton.  However you would want a fast weapon in your primary so that you could lay down the fastest possible dmg in your primary.  All things being equal by lvl 60 regardless of speed the baton and your 2nd hand would be about equal in speed.  But the ratio of your hands is now suppassed the baton so you would drop it about lvl 40 or so.  <br><br>Let's assume you actually couldn't buy this item.  You get this baton about lvl 20 in the crypt.  It's a shame but that's how the game is set.  Well this is when your fists start actually doing secondary damage effectively.  So for the next 20 lvls the baton is actually a good thing.  After lvl 40 it's a toss up.  And, at lvl 50 it's pretty clear the baton sucks for you.  <br><br>BUT, this doesn't apply to iksors at all.  Sorry for you, go clean your scales or something.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>1 Replies</td></tr>
