	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>684 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Hate to disagree, but I have to disagree.&nbsp;&nbsp;FB is better than fist in primary hand until Level 55, and better than fist in secondary until Level 45.  This link tells you all you need to know.<br><br><a href="http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html" target=_new>http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html</a><br><br>There is a damage bonus in primary hand starting at lvl 25 that benefits faster weapons more.  If all you have is one baton, put it in your primary hand.  But you should try to get something for your off-hand.  My personal favorite is a Cane of Tranquil but it costs 1K and so is probably out of your range.  An Essence of Dol is pretty cheap, weighs nothing, equips off-hand, and outclasses off-hand fist until the mid-30s.<br><br>A fighting baton is certainly not lame-o, and can serve a monk VERY well until level 40+.  This applies to both human and iksar.<br><br>Good hunting to ya!<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 44th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro</p>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></tr>
