	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1468><span id= >Thelonius</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I agree with Keyeluke. FB is good til 55 and FB + fist is a full 20% better than Fist + Fist at 45. 618 dpm vs. 516 dpm according to Copeland's analyzer. I think the tinnidar tables, while excellent, tend to underestimate slightly the faster weapon, due to the fact that tinnidar is based on the modal damage calculation. I think you also have to consider that your checks for dbl will come off the 20 dly in primary vs the fist dly at lvl X, which is&nbsp;&nbsp;lower til 55 - another benefit. I'd also give some thought to the fact that the FB will give skill checks more often, so in theory you'll get your 1hb up faster. Hence the beauty of the BamBo. In a group you may want to manage your agro by not using the baton, depending on who you're grouped with. A person might also consider a higher dmg, slower dly, 2hb if you're working against a dmg shield of some sort, or for simple agro list control, I suppose.<br><br>With regards to EoD, Copeland's shows it as a wash at level 45 [ I find this hard to believe ], but parsing my old logs shows that EoD was basically gone at 35 for all practical purposes. I sold it at level 39. 0.1 wt was nice though.<br><br>CoT is wonderful in secondary. Even at lvl 50 FB + CoT is about 5% better than FB + FB, and 20% better than Fist + Fist.<br><br>For those of you without Copeland's, try<br><br><a href="http://www.geocities.com/copelandeq/weaponanalyzer.html" target=_new>http://www.geocities.com/copelandeq/weaponanalyzer.html</a><br><br>has a few rough spots, but it gives you somethings to consider. I think it's also avail. through monkly-business.<br><br> The FB is a very nice weapon, nothing better for 500 pp today. I'm not sure that a group of 22's could get to lumpy to get it though. Second floor of Dalnir's is a long way.....</p>&nbsp;<br>Thelonius monk</td></tr>
